WEBVTT

00:06.340 --> 00:09.343
[waves crashing]

00:15.891 --> 00:18.894
[seagull cawing]

00:23.733 --> 00:26.736
[tense music]

00:26.736 --> 00:33.743
♪ ♪

00:36.120 --> 00:37.663
[gasps]

00:40.082 --> 00:41.167
Oscar?

00:42.501 --> 00:45.546
- What happened?
- You passed out.

00:45.546 --> 00:46.922
You've been out for a while.

00:46.922 --> 00:48.466
I brought you
close to the ocean.

00:48.466 --> 00:51.010
It's kind of like
the fountain.

00:51.010 --> 00:53.846
[waves crashing]

00:53.846 --> 00:55.139
[Oscar] My God.

00:56.891 --> 00:59.602
I was so tired.

00:59.602 --> 01:01.353
I don't even remember.

01:01.353 --> 01:03.564
Well, you stormed into our
party like a crazy person

01:03.564 --> 01:07.067
and said a bunch
of mean shit to me.

01:07.067 --> 01:08.819
Like what?

01:10.029 --> 01:12.656
Well, you told me
I was a home wrecker,

01:12.656 --> 01:16.952
and you also said
I was selfish and evil

01:16.952 --> 01:18.871
and am a poser.

01:19.997 --> 01:23.751
Well...

01:23.751 --> 01:25.294
great.

01:25.294 --> 01:26.462
Because I do think
those things,

01:26.462 --> 01:28.005
and I'm glad I said them.

01:28.005 --> 01:30.841
What?
Are you serious?

01:30.841 --> 01:34.386
Yes, you did a cruel
and horrible thing to me.

01:34.386 --> 01:35.930
You just ran off
with someone else.

01:35.930 --> 01:38.265
By the way,
what's going on there?

01:38.265 --> 01:40.684
- Are you a lesbian now?
- No.

01:40.684 --> 01:43.103
I mean...

01:43.103 --> 01:44.980
Kase and I just have a very...

01:44.980 --> 01:48.025
deep understanding
of each other.

01:48.025 --> 01:49.443
So you're not
sleeping with her?

01:49.443 --> 01:52.404
No, but you know what?
Even if I was,

01:52.404 --> 01:54.615
it wouldn't necessarily
make me gay.

01:54.615 --> 01:57.284
- Sexuality is a spectrum.
- Oh, shut up.

01:57.284 --> 01:58.744
No, I will not shut up.

01:58.744 --> 02:00.371
You know,
it wasn't an easy decision.

02:00.371 --> 02:03.207
Do you know how hard it was
for me to leave?

02:03.207 --> 02:04.708
No, I don't,
because you didn't

02:04.708 --> 02:06.335
come to me like an adult
to talk to me about it.

02:06.335 --> 02:08.712
Anytime I ever tried
to talk to you about it,

02:08.712 --> 02:10.130
you avoided the conversation.

02:10.130 --> 02:11.966
- That's not true.
- It was always the case

02:11.966 --> 02:14.718
when we were alive, and it got
even worse after we died.

02:14.718 --> 02:16.804
- Not true.
- You're doing it right now.

02:16.804 --> 02:18.639
- Disagree.
- Oh, my God.

02:18.639 --> 02:20.182
This is pointless.

02:20.182 --> 02:23.143
So...so is that why
you came all this way?

02:23.143 --> 02:25.271
You just came here to tell me
that I'm a bad person?

02:25.271 --> 02:26.897
- Yes.
- Oh.

02:26.897 --> 02:29.149
Also, I never cared
for your sister.

02:29.149 --> 02:30.526
Kathy or Stephanie?

02:30.526 --> 02:32.403
Well, of course
I'm talking about Kathy.

02:32.403 --> 02:33.696
Everyone loves Stephanie.

02:33.696 --> 02:35.114
She owns that
wonderful cupcake shop.

02:35.114 --> 02:36.490
Are we done?

02:36.490 --> 02:38.409
Have you finished
getting all your

02:38.409 --> 02:40.035
childish shit out of the way?

02:40.035 --> 02:42.204
Now that you mention it, no.

02:42.204 --> 02:43.873
I'd like a divorce.

02:43.873 --> 02:47.209
What?
Are you joking?

02:47.209 --> 02:50.212
You realize we're dead, right?

02:50.212 --> 02:53.424
- I, Oscar Hoffman...
- Oh, my God.

02:53.424 --> 02:57.261
...do solemnly swear
to divorce June Hoffman

02:57.261 --> 02:59.763
on the grounds of desertion
and emotional violence.

02:59.763 --> 03:02.266
- This is so stupid.
- Just do it.

03:02.266 --> 03:04.476
Oh, oh, and then we're done?
Great.

03:04.476 --> 03:07.021
I, June Hoffman,
do solemnly swear

03:07.021 --> 03:08.814
to divorce Oscar Hoffman
on the grounds of being

03:08.814 --> 03:10.316
a passive-aggressive dick.

03:10.316 --> 03:12.902
Okay, mine was more legal.

03:12.902 --> 03:14.653
But I guess that's it.

03:14.653 --> 03:17.489
- All right, officially.
- Great, officially.

03:17.489 --> 03:19.909
I'm gonna go back
to Riverside, all right?

03:19.909 --> 03:21.535
Where people are nice.

03:21.535 --> 03:23.412
- Mm-hmm.
- So...

03:23.412 --> 03:25.831
- good-bye forever.
- Good-bye.

03:27.207 --> 03:30.210
[somber music]

03:30.210 --> 03:37.217
♪ ♪

03:40.179 --> 03:43.265
Jesus Christ!

03:43.265 --> 03:44.600
What's going on here?

03:44.600 --> 03:45.893
Getting ready
for The Cleansing.

03:45.893 --> 03:47.770
- What is that?
- Once a year,

03:47.770 --> 03:49.772
we take all our belongings
out to the beach,

03:49.772 --> 03:52.983
build a giant pyre,
and burn them.

03:52.983 --> 03:54.860
Fuck!

03:54.860 --> 03:56.654
Why do you do that?

03:56.654 --> 04:00.366
It's a reminder
that we should always forget.

04:00.366 --> 04:03.118
- What?
- Objects that were once

04:03.118 --> 04:06.455
so permanent
are now ephemeral to us.

04:06.455 --> 04:09.041
We were like butterflies,
and now they are.

04:09.041 --> 04:11.126
Such an irony, no?

04:11.126 --> 04:13.212
Plus, a fire on the beach
probably looks pretty cool.

04:13.212 --> 04:14.838
[laughs]

04:14.838 --> 04:17.549
June, sometimes the things
you say are stupid,

04:17.549 --> 04:19.426
but I still enjoy them.

04:19.426 --> 04:22.471
What a gift that is.
Treasure it.

04:22.471 --> 04:25.641
Thank you.
I will treasure it.

04:27.059 --> 04:28.811
Shit!

04:28.811 --> 04:30.270
[exhales]

04:30.270 --> 04:31.647
I'm getting out of here.

04:31.647 --> 04:33.565
You guys can hang out
or whatever.

04:35.859 --> 04:38.862
[jazz music playing]

04:38.862 --> 04:45.869
♪ ♪

04:47.454 --> 04:49.790
I'm actually a little jealous
that you got to get divorced.

04:49.790 --> 04:51.333
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

04:51.333 --> 04:53.460
So are you doing okay
with all of it?

04:53.460 --> 04:56.005
- I actually am.
- [chuckles]

04:56.005 --> 04:57.423
I swear, I feel like a weight

04:57.423 --> 04:59.508
has been lifted
off my shoulders.

04:59.508 --> 05:01.385
- I feel great.
- Me too.

05:01.385 --> 05:03.178
[both laugh]

05:03.178 --> 05:05.389
This party is amazing.

05:05.389 --> 05:07.599
I think it's the best party
I've ever been to.

05:07.599 --> 05:09.476
Oh, I don't know.

05:09.476 --> 05:11.979
I was once invited
to my nephew's bar mitzvah

05:11.979 --> 05:14.440
where the theme
was restaurants.

05:14.440 --> 05:16.233
[both laugh]

05:16.233 --> 05:23.240
♪ ♪

05:25.242 --> 05:27.494
- Think I'm gonna head home.
- Aw, really?

05:27.494 --> 05:30.664
Yeah, I'm tired.

05:30.664 --> 05:33.125
If dead people get hangovers,
I'm fucked.

05:33.125 --> 05:36.128
[both laugh]

05:36.128 --> 05:40.299
- Do you mind if I stay?
- No, of course not.

05:41.633 --> 05:42.885
- Bye.
- Bye.

05:42.885 --> 05:49.892
♪ ♪

06:01.612 --> 06:02.946
[music stops]

06:02.946 --> 06:05.741
Hey, everyone,
I know we've heard a lot

06:05.741 --> 06:07.785
of really great music
here tonight,

06:07.785 --> 06:11.622
but, uh, here's
what I consider to be

06:11.622 --> 06:15.125
the greatest song of all time.

06:15.125 --> 06:16.668
[man] Two, three.

06:16.668 --> 06:18.837
♪ This is how we do it ♪

06:18.837 --> 06:22.549
[playing Montell Jordan's
"This Is How We Do It"]

06:22.549 --> 06:25.552
♪ Sha-la-la, la-la-la-la ♪

06:25.552 --> 06:27.846
♪ ♪

06:27.846 --> 06:32.017
♪ This is how we do it,
it's Friday night ♪

06:32.017 --> 06:34.561
♪ And I feel all right ♪

06:34.561 --> 06:36.688
♪ The party's here
on the west side ♪

06:36.688 --> 06:39.358
♪ So I reach for my 40,
and I tip it up ♪

06:39.358 --> 06:41.985
♪ Designated driver,
take the keys to my truck ♪

06:41.985 --> 06:44.029
♪ Hit the 'Shaw
because I'm faded ♪

06:44.029 --> 06:46.448
♪ Honeys on the street say,
"Monty, yo, we made it" ♪

06:46.448 --> 06:47.866
♪ It feels so good... ♪

06:47.866 --> 06:50.661
Hi, Marisol.
It's Gregory!

06:50.661 --> 06:52.746
[all]
♪ This is how we do it ♪

06:52.746 --> 06:56.083
♪ All the gangbangers
forgot about the drive-by ♪

06:56.083 --> 06:59.628
♪ You gotta get your groove on
before you go get paid ♪

06:59.628 --> 07:02.214
♪ So tip up your cup,
throw your hands up ♪

07:02.214 --> 07:04.424
♪ Let me hear the party say ♪

07:04.424 --> 07:06.677
♪ I'm kind of buzzed,
and it's all because ♪

07:06.677 --> 07:08.762
[all] ♪ This is how we do it ♪

07:08.762 --> 07:11.306
♪ South Central
does it like nobody does ♪

07:11.306 --> 07:13.600
[all] ♪ This is how we do it ♪

07:13.600 --> 07:15.936
♪ ♪

07:15.936 --> 07:18.730
♪ This is how we do it ♪

07:18.730 --> 07:20.566
Here, you finish it.
Don't screw it up.

07:20.566 --> 07:22.442
[all] ♪ This is how we do it ♪♪

07:22.442 --> 07:26.697
[dramatic music]

07:26.697 --> 07:27.948
Hey!

07:27.948 --> 07:29.408
I see you!
Get back here!

07:29.408 --> 07:32.035
♪ ♪

07:32.035 --> 07:34.663
It's not me!
I'm someone else!

07:34.663 --> 07:37.207
You're not gonna get away.
You got fucked-up feet.

07:37.207 --> 07:40.043
♪ ♪

07:40.043 --> 07:42.212
[both grunt]

07:44.173 --> 07:46.925
What are you still doing here?
You said you were leaving.

07:46.925 --> 07:50.304
I tried to leave.
But I couldn't.

07:50.304 --> 07:52.139
What do you mean you couldn't?

07:55.142 --> 07:57.436
What am I looking for?
Where are we going?

07:57.436 --> 08:00.731
Just wait.

08:00.731 --> 08:02.608
How's Kase?

08:02.608 --> 08:06.612
- She's fine.
- Mm-hmm.

08:06.612 --> 08:09.156
You guys ever share shirts?

08:09.156 --> 08:11.950
We have our own clothes.

08:11.950 --> 08:14.620
It's not that weird a question.
You are around the same size.

08:14.620 --> 08:15.996
You know what?
We don't have to talk.

08:15.996 --> 08:16.830
[man] Hello there.

08:16.830 --> 08:18.207
- Shit!
- Jesus!

08:18.207 --> 08:20.792
- Where are you headed?
- Nowhere.

08:20.792 --> 08:23.212
That's not true.
I'm not going anywhere.

08:23.212 --> 08:25.047
He's going back to Riverside.

08:25.881 --> 08:29.051
- I don't think he is.
- We've been over this.

08:29.051 --> 08:31.428
- He and I have been over this.
- What do you mean?

08:31.428 --> 08:35.724
Sir, I don't know
what your exact deal is,

08:35.724 --> 08:38.518
but this is my ex-husband,
and he needs to go back

08:38.518 --> 08:40.312
to Riverside so he can
get the hell out of my life.

08:40.312 --> 08:43.232
I'm afraid that's impossible.

08:43.232 --> 08:45.567
All roads lead to Oceanside.

08:45.567 --> 08:47.569
We've met before.

08:47.569 --> 08:49.571
I feel like
you said that to me last time.

08:49.571 --> 08:50.989
Did he say that
to you before too?

08:50.989 --> 08:53.700
I think he did, yes.
Um, please, sir.

08:53.700 --> 08:56.954
I won't tell anyone
about Oceanside, okay?

08:56.954 --> 08:58.956
I'll just zip it right up
if that's the problem.

08:58.956 --> 09:01.250
But you got to understand,
this is a bad situation.

09:01.250 --> 09:03.085
- Yeah.
- All right?

09:03.085 --> 09:07.005
This isn't the kind of divorce
where we're still friends.

09:07.005 --> 09:09.424
- She had an emotional affair.
- I did.

09:09.424 --> 09:14.346
You got to understand, right?
I mean, have you been married?

09:14.346 --> 09:15.639
Divorced?

09:17.933 --> 09:21.645
All roads lead to Oceanside.

09:21.645 --> 09:24.439
- Great.
- I told you.

09:24.439 --> 09:26.358
- I told her.
- He did.

09:26.358 --> 09:28.819
But she wouldn't believe me,
so I had to show her in person.

09:28.819 --> 09:30.279
It's true.

09:30.279 --> 09:31.863
You know how it is, right?

09:31.863 --> 09:33.699
You know, right, wives?

09:33.699 --> 09:34.533
[chuckles]

09:37.411 --> 09:39.746
I mean, if you're married.

09:39.746 --> 09:44.376
I'm getting more of a
bachelor vibe from you, so...

09:44.376 --> 09:47.212
I don't know.

09:47.212 --> 09:49.631
All right.

09:49.631 --> 09:53.051
What's in your briefcase,
by the way?

09:53.051 --> 09:55.470
I've been wondering.

09:55.470 --> 09:57.306
- Is it just papers?
- We should go.

09:57.306 --> 09:58.890
Yeah, I think you're right.

09:58.890 --> 10:01.101
- All right, thank you.
- No.

10:03.186 --> 10:06.189
[soft music]

10:06.189 --> 10:10.152
♪ ♪

10:10.152 --> 10:12.779
- Well, this is me.
- What?

10:12.779 --> 10:14.614
This is where
you've been living?

10:14.614 --> 10:16.074
Well, what else can I do?

10:16.074 --> 10:18.744
I don't want to be
anywhere near where you are.

10:18.744 --> 10:20.746
So, what, are you just
gonna stay here forever?

10:20.746 --> 10:22.581
Definitely not.

10:22.581 --> 10:24.916
I have a plan.
Let me show you something.

10:28.837 --> 10:31.006
There she is.

10:31.006 --> 10:34.092
- There what is?
- It's a boat.

10:34.092 --> 10:37.596
That's not a boat.
That's, like, three logs.

10:37.596 --> 10:40.390
Well, it's not a boat yet.
I'm still working on it.

10:40.390 --> 10:43.310
He said all roads
lead to Oceanside.

10:43.310 --> 10:44.978
He didn't say anything
about the sea.

10:44.978 --> 10:47.481
Do you even know
how to build a boat?

10:47.481 --> 10:50.067
Yeah, I built a lot of
model ships when I was a kid.

10:50.067 --> 10:52.778
It's the same principle.
Just have to up the scale.

10:52.778 --> 10:56.031
- Oh, Jesus.
- I can do it.

10:56.031 --> 10:58.033
I just need
some more materials.

10:58.033 --> 10:59.910
Yeah, like what?

10:59.910 --> 11:04.498
A knife, a sail,
maybe some more rope.

11:04.498 --> 11:06.124
I mean, I could use
a lot of stuff.

11:06.124 --> 11:08.251
This is basically
just three logs.

11:10.462 --> 11:12.547
Maybe you can help me.

11:12.547 --> 11:14.383
Why would I do that?

11:14.383 --> 11:17.677
Do you want me
out of here or not?

11:17.677 --> 11:22.140
It's gonna take forever if I
have to keep sneaking around.

11:22.140 --> 11:23.600
- I don't know.
- Come on.

11:23.600 --> 11:25.519
We don't even
have to see each other.

11:25.519 --> 11:27.270
Okay, there's this flat rock

11:27.270 --> 11:28.897
right around the bend
over there; you can't miss it.

11:28.897 --> 11:31.817
Just leave it there
and I'll pick it up.

11:34.236 --> 11:35.946
Yeah, sure, okay, fine.
I'll help you.

11:35.946 --> 11:37.447
Great.

11:37.447 --> 11:39.783
But only because I don't
want you distracting me

11:39.783 --> 11:41.743
from putting on
a fucking awesome concert

11:41.743 --> 11:43.370
for all my friends.

11:43.370 --> 11:46.248
- It wasn't that awesome.
- Shut up. I was great.

11:46.248 --> 11:47.624
You ran out of breath too much.

11:47.624 --> 11:49.042
Ugh.

11:49.042 --> 11:52.045
[tense music]

11:52.045 --> 11:59.052
♪ ♪

12:03.723 --> 12:05.600
- Hey.
- Morning.

12:05.600 --> 12:07.269
You just getting home?

12:07.269 --> 12:09.729
Uh, yeah, I got caught up.

12:09.729 --> 12:11.815
Uh-huh.

12:11.815 --> 12:13.775
I'll, um...I'll catch up
with you in a bit.

12:13.775 --> 12:14.776
Okay.

12:33.420 --> 12:35.922
I can see you.

12:35.922 --> 12:38.675
Oh, you're still here?

12:38.675 --> 12:41.511
I think it's pretty obvious
I'm still here, yeah.

12:41.511 --> 12:43.763
I was just checking the time.

12:43.763 --> 12:46.349
I built a sundial down there.

12:46.349 --> 12:48.059
It's between 2:00 and 7:00.

12:48.059 --> 12:50.604
- It's 11:00 a.m.
- Oh.

12:50.604 --> 12:51.938
It's cloudy.

12:53.315 --> 12:55.901
So I brought your bedsheet.

12:57.777 --> 13:00.155
It's a little small.

13:00.155 --> 13:03.867
It would maybe work for
a topsail but not a mainsail.

13:03.867 --> 13:06.995
Sorry to disappoint you,
Master and Commander.

13:06.995 --> 13:09.456
How's the boat coming?

13:15.795 --> 13:17.589
Wow.

13:17.589 --> 13:20.300
You actually made a decent
amount of progress.

13:20.300 --> 13:22.469
That's so surprising?

13:22.469 --> 13:23.845
No.

13:23.845 --> 13:26.389
Well, it sounded like
you were surprised.

13:26.389 --> 13:28.975
- You said "actually."
- God, Oscar.

13:28.975 --> 13:31.061
I was trying to
give you a compliment.

13:31.061 --> 13:33.730
I mean, it still
looks very shitty, okay?

13:33.730 --> 13:35.941
Is that...is that better?
Does that help?

13:35.941 --> 13:38.693
I'm just saying,
I was right and you were wrong.

13:38.693 --> 13:40.695
I told you I could build it.

13:40.695 --> 13:45.075
I just needed to flush out the
bones of what I had, and I did.

13:45.075 --> 13:46.868
Okay, great.

13:52.958 --> 13:54.626
Actually, you know what?

13:54.626 --> 13:57.504
Since we're never gonna
see each other again,

13:57.504 --> 14:00.423
it's not "flush out."

14:00.423 --> 14:02.092
It's "flesh out."

14:02.092 --> 14:04.761
- What?
- You always say "flush out."

14:04.761 --> 14:07.222
It's "flesh out,"
you add flesh to something

14:07.222 --> 14:09.224
to make it more full.

14:09.224 --> 14:10.642
"Flush out"
doesn't make any sense.

14:10.642 --> 14:12.102
You just sound like an idiot.

14:16.815 --> 14:18.525
I've heard it both ways.

14:18.525 --> 14:20.902
Yeah, the way that you say it
and the correct way

14:20.902 --> 14:22.737
that everyone else
in the world says it.

14:22.737 --> 14:28.618
Flesh, flesh, flesh, fleshed,
flesh, fleshed,

14:28.618 --> 14:30.120
fleshed out, I fleshed it out,

14:30.120 --> 14:31.496
the committee
fleshed out the proposal.

14:31.496 --> 14:33.123
Okay, yes, I see
what you're saying.

14:33.123 --> 14:35.584
Great, great.

14:35.584 --> 14:38.211
Well, that's settled, then.

14:38.211 --> 14:39.796
You should try
to be ready soon.

14:39.796 --> 14:41.590
We're doing this thing
called The Cleansing,

14:41.590 --> 14:43.216
and everyone
will be distracted,

14:43.216 --> 14:44.718
so it'll be a good time
for you to sneak out.

14:44.718 --> 14:47.220
What's The Cleansing?
Is that...

14:47.220 --> 14:49.055
is that ethnic cleansing?

14:49.055 --> 14:52.559
No, no, it's a lot
of fires on the beach

14:52.559 --> 14:54.519
and dancing and shit,
probably.

14:54.519 --> 14:55.729
No genocide.

14:55.729 --> 14:57.731
Thank God.

14:57.731 --> 14:59.399
All right, I'll be ready.

14:59.399 --> 15:02.694
And then this...
will all be over.

15:02.694 --> 15:04.362
Yeah.

15:04.362 --> 15:07.032
- Great.
- Wonderful.

15:07.032 --> 15:08.366
Okay.

15:17.417 --> 15:20.378
[♪ Henri Texier: "Amir"]

15:20.378 --> 15:23.798
♪ ♪

15:23.798 --> 15:26.051
[vocalizing]

15:26.051 --> 15:33.058
♪ ♪

15:47.947 --> 15:54.954
♪ ♪

16:25.360 --> 16:32.367
♪ ♪

16:59.352 --> 17:06.359
♪ ♪

17:11.698 --> 17:13.742
Here's your ham.

17:13.742 --> 17:15.243
Not sure
what you wanted this for.

17:15.243 --> 17:17.120
Are you gonna eat it
on the boat?

17:17.120 --> 17:19.414
What?
I wrote "hammer."

17:21.750 --> 17:25.336
Oh, no,
the seagulls got the "-mer."

17:25.336 --> 17:28.673
Damn it, Oscar,
that ham was heavy too.

17:28.673 --> 17:31.968
Well, it's here.
Might as well eat it, I guess.

17:32.886 --> 17:34.053
Knock yourself out.

17:46.441 --> 17:47.567
You want some?

17:49.027 --> 17:51.112
I guess. I did
carry it all this way.

17:53.656 --> 17:56.659
I don't have any utensils,
so you have to use your hands.

17:56.659 --> 17:58.119
That's all right.

18:04.042 --> 18:05.043
It's not bad.

18:07.086 --> 18:08.880
How sandy
is your piece right now?

18:08.880 --> 18:11.007
- Very.
- Mine too.

18:17.055 --> 18:19.015
But food on the beach is tough.

18:20.600 --> 18:23.770
It's a weird place
to be eating, you know?

18:23.770 --> 18:25.480
It's kind of hard
to thread that needle.

18:25.480 --> 18:27.732
Yeah, like...

18:27.732 --> 18:31.569
if your food is handheld,
it's going to get sandy.

18:31.569 --> 18:34.489
But if you need utensils,
well, you're lugging around

18:34.489 --> 18:36.074
a bag of forks and knives.

18:36.074 --> 18:38.076
Mm.

18:45.875 --> 18:48.378
I wonder...

18:48.378 --> 18:51.798
What the all-time
best beach food is.

18:55.844 --> 18:58.179
What about ice cream?

18:58.179 --> 19:01.266
The beach is hot,
and ice cream melts.

19:01.266 --> 19:03.810
I mean, the second
you start on that cone,

19:03.810 --> 19:05.311
you're trying
to beat the buzzer.

19:05.311 --> 19:06.604
You're licking
around the edges,

19:06.604 --> 19:08.439
trying to stem the tide.

19:08.439 --> 19:10.108
I mean, you're not
handing me a snack.

19:10.108 --> 19:12.694
You're handing me
a time bomb.

19:12.694 --> 19:15.655
Good point, all right.

19:15.655 --> 19:19.450
What about churros?
It's portable, delicious.

19:19.450 --> 19:22.787
A lot of carbs,
gives you energy for swimming.

19:22.787 --> 19:24.122
Are you insane?

19:24.122 --> 19:25.790
Churros are covered
in a substance

19:25.790 --> 19:27.500
that looks exactly like sand.

19:27.500 --> 19:30.211
What's sand?
What's cinnamon sugar?

19:30.211 --> 19:32.171
I don't know.
I guess I'm eating both.

19:32.171 --> 19:34.048
[laughs]

19:34.048 --> 19:36.092
All right, genius,
what's your brilliant idea?

19:36.092 --> 19:37.635
Oh, I'm not here to be helpful.

19:37.635 --> 19:39.387
I'm just here to shoot down
any ideas you've got.

19:39.387 --> 19:41.764
Ah, all right.

19:41.764 --> 19:43.808
Wait.

19:43.808 --> 19:47.312
The perfect beach food is...

19:47.312 --> 19:48.605
buffalo wings.

19:48.605 --> 19:50.064
[laughs]

19:50.064 --> 19:52.066
Super saucy, sticky,

19:52.066 --> 19:53.776
really spicy
for that hot beach weather,

19:53.776 --> 19:55.820
- Oh.
- Then when you're done,

19:55.820 --> 19:58.698
you feel awful and you're left
with a gross pile of bones.

19:58.698 --> 20:01.117
Ooh, plus, they'll
probably give you diarrhea.

20:01.117 --> 20:03.202
Great news, you're doing that
at the beach.

20:03.202 --> 20:04.245
[both laugh]

20:04.245 --> 20:06.581
You know, honestly...

20:06.581 --> 20:08.750
I kind of do
want wings right now.

20:08.750 --> 20:10.793
Mmm, yeah, that sounds good.

20:12.128 --> 20:14.464
No offense, ham,
but I wish you were wings.

20:14.464 --> 20:15.798
Sorry, buddy.

20:15.798 --> 20:17.133
[laughs]

20:17.133 --> 20:18.968
Wait, what'd you
just call me?

20:18.968 --> 20:20.595
You don't need to use
that kind of language.

20:20.595 --> 20:22.722
He just called you
a fucking asshole.

20:22.722 --> 20:25.183
[laughs]

20:25.183 --> 20:26.434
What are you, anyway?

20:26.434 --> 20:28.353
What part of the body
are you, ham?

20:28.353 --> 20:31.940
- Yeah, ham.
- Are you a hock?

20:31.940 --> 20:33.733
- Oh, now you're quiet, got it.
- Oh, oh, oh.

20:33.733 --> 20:34.984
- You have nothing to say now?
- Now, you're quiet.

20:34.984 --> 20:36.444
- Now you're quiet?
- Okay.

20:36.444 --> 20:38.404
- Oh, fine, that makes sense.
- Yeah.

20:38.404 --> 20:40.531
What are you doing?

20:40.531 --> 20:43.660
Oh, hey, I didn't
hear you walk up.

20:43.660 --> 20:45.411
- Hi.
- I thought you left.

20:45.411 --> 20:46.746
Why are you still here?

20:46.746 --> 20:48.289
I couldn't leave.

20:48.289 --> 20:50.291
The guy with the briefcase
wouldn't let me.

20:50.291 --> 20:54.295
Well, then why are you two
sitting here yukking it up?

20:54.295 --> 20:56.506
This was the first time
we sat down and talked,

20:56.506 --> 20:58.716
and it was just about nothing.

20:58.716 --> 21:01.177
Didn't seem like nothing.

21:01.177 --> 21:03.972
You know what? We're all
too dead for this shit.

21:03.972 --> 21:06.057
You two do what you want.

21:07.809 --> 21:10.561
He and I are done.

21:10.561 --> 21:13.773
Really, we're done.
Come on.

21:13.773 --> 21:16.776
[soft music]

21:16.776 --> 21:23.783
♪ ♪

21:26.703 --> 21:29.706
[indistinct chatter]

21:32.333 --> 21:34.002
[Kase]
Look at this thing.

21:36.212 --> 21:38.840
Can you believe
we're here?

21:38.840 --> 21:41.134
It's pretty crazy.

21:41.134 --> 21:48.141
♪ ♪

22:09.203 --> 22:12.206
[tense music]

22:12.206 --> 22:19.213
♪ ♪

22:39.192 --> 22:41.027
Hey.

22:41.027 --> 22:43.112
I got a hammer for you.

22:44.655 --> 22:46.324
Oh, okay.

22:48.534 --> 22:50.787
Let's see if this works better
than my rock system.

22:57.043 --> 23:00.213
Yup, it definitely does.

23:00.213 --> 23:01.756
I was right to ask for this.

23:03.925 --> 23:06.260
All right, that's it.

23:06.260 --> 23:09.597
She's ready to go.

23:09.597 --> 23:12.517
So you're really
gonna do this, huh?

23:12.517 --> 23:14.519
Yeah.

23:14.519 --> 23:17.897
Gonna leave tomorrow at dawn,
when the tide shifts.

23:18.689 --> 23:23.111
You do know that the ocean
is a very big place, right?

23:23.111 --> 23:26.155
I mean, look at this shit.

23:26.155 --> 23:28.866
Yeah, I know.

23:28.866 --> 23:31.119
I mean, I can do this stuff.

23:31.119 --> 23:34.372
I built this boat, you know,
from sticks and garbage.

23:34.372 --> 23:36.207
I walked all the way here

23:36.207 --> 23:37.583
without ever touching
a Current.

23:39.961 --> 23:43.464
You know, I think
the whole time I've known you,

23:43.464 --> 23:45.800
I've underestimated you
a little bit.

23:47.051 --> 23:49.804
Yeah, I think
that might be true.

23:49.804 --> 23:52.765
Honestly, it's probably
because I used you

23:52.765 --> 23:54.725
as an excuse
a lot of the time.

23:54.725 --> 23:56.769
What do you mean?

23:56.769 --> 24:00.690
Well, sometimes I blamed you
for being in the way

24:00.690 --> 24:05.611
of me becoming
this hypothetical

24:05.611 --> 24:09.574
amazing,
new version of myself.

24:11.367 --> 24:16.497
But I was never
gonna become that person.

24:16.497 --> 24:19.500
Do you remember
that awesome new job

24:19.500 --> 24:21.794
I told you I got
after you died?

24:21.794 --> 24:23.754
Yeah.

24:23.754 --> 24:26.924
The truth is, uh...

24:26.924 --> 24:28.968
when I went to interview
for the job,

24:28.968 --> 24:31.846
I totally freaked out
and ran away.

24:31.846 --> 24:36.517
And I only got the job
because, basically,

24:36.517 --> 24:38.644
everyone that worked
at my company got arrested,

24:38.644 --> 24:41.272
and I was the only person left.

24:41.272 --> 24:43.524
I knew that place was shady.

24:45.276 --> 24:47.737
You weren't the problem.

24:47.737 --> 24:49.655
I was.

24:49.655 --> 24:52.658
It was just a lot easier
to blame you.

24:54.827 --> 24:57.413
And I'm sorry for that.

24:57.413 --> 25:02.043
I mean, it's nice of you
to say those things, but...

25:02.043 --> 25:05.171
you weren't
totally wrong to blame me.

25:06.380 --> 25:09.133
I never made it easy for you.

25:09.133 --> 25:12.011
There were times where
I knew you weren't happy,

25:12.011 --> 25:14.388
and there were times
where I wasn't happy,

25:14.388 --> 25:18.392
but I was always afraid
to talk to you about it.

25:18.392 --> 25:21.520
- Why?
- I don't know.

25:21.520 --> 25:22.897
I think,
in the back of my mind,

25:22.897 --> 25:25.024
I was scared
that if we really did

25:25.024 --> 25:27.193
talk about our problems,
you'd realize

25:27.193 --> 25:30.112
that you were
way out of my league.

25:30.112 --> 25:33.449
Really, even
after all this time?

25:33.449 --> 25:37.203
Yeah, I know it sounds stupid.

25:37.203 --> 25:39.497
God, I ended up making
everything worse

25:39.497 --> 25:42.833
and pushing you away.

25:42.833 --> 25:44.669
God, and here we are.

25:47.922 --> 25:51.717
- So I'm sorry too.
- Thank you.

25:51.717 --> 25:53.094
You're welcome.

25:56.347 --> 25:59.767
- All right.
- All right, um...

25:59.767 --> 26:02.478
- good-bye.
- Bye.

26:05.648 --> 26:06.649
Hey.

26:08.734 --> 26:11.904
I think we just had our first
honest conversation ever.

26:14.031 --> 26:17.159
Too bad it wasn't
when we were alive.

26:17.159 --> 26:19.161
[chuckles softly]
Yeah.

26:19.161 --> 26:22.164
[dramatic music]

26:22.164 --> 26:29.171
♪ ♪

26:29.171 --> 26:32.174
[indistinct chatter]

26:35.136 --> 26:37.138
- Hello.
- Hello.

26:40.558 --> 26:41.809
- Hey.
- Hey.

26:41.809 --> 26:43.352
Where were you?

26:43.352 --> 26:45.855
Uh, I needed to give Oscar
one more thing.

26:48.232 --> 26:49.942
He'll be gone in the morning.

26:52.153 --> 26:55.406
Everyone, gather around.

26:55.406 --> 26:57.366
The time has come.

26:57.366 --> 27:00.619
The Cleansing has begun!

27:00.619 --> 27:02.121
[upbeat percussion]

27:02.121 --> 27:04.290
[people cheering]

27:04.290 --> 27:11.297
♪ ♪

27:35.988 --> 27:37.573
[Kase]
Hey, there you are.

27:37.573 --> 27:39.325
[laughs]

27:39.325 --> 27:43.954
Oh, whew.
I need a breather.

27:43.954 --> 27:45.790
Gregory lit my face on fire.

27:45.790 --> 27:47.166
- What?
- Yeah.

27:47.166 --> 27:49.210
- We can do that?
- Yeah.

27:49.210 --> 27:52.296
- Wow, how'd it feel?
- It was okay.

27:52.296 --> 27:54.548
It's kind of like
eating Thai food.

27:54.548 --> 27:56.217
Huh.

27:56.217 --> 27:58.219
Yeah, I never knew
what to order at Thai places.

27:58.219 --> 27:59.970
Every time I tried
to order a salad,

27:59.970 --> 28:02.765
it always ended up being
really spicy meat, somehow.

28:02.765 --> 28:04.934
[laughing] Yeah.

28:04.934 --> 28:08.020
Hey, are you starting
to forget things?

28:08.020 --> 28:12.274
- Yeah, a little bit.
- Hell, me too.

28:12.274 --> 28:14.402
This is a little crazy,

28:14.402 --> 28:16.028
but I'm having
trouble remembering

28:16.028 --> 28:18.406
what job I had
when I was alive.

28:18.406 --> 28:20.533
You definitely told me.

28:20.533 --> 28:23.244
Um, but I think it was
so boring, I forgot too.

28:23.244 --> 28:24.537
[both laugh]

28:24.537 --> 28:26.747
Good.

28:26.747 --> 28:28.582
To hell with that shit.

28:28.582 --> 28:29.917
Right?

28:34.213 --> 28:36.215
I'm really glad we came.

28:38.801 --> 28:40.219
Hello.

28:40.219 --> 28:41.637
- Hi.
- Hi.

28:41.637 --> 28:45.015
Kase, I need someone
to light me on fire,

28:45.015 --> 28:48.018
and I really want it to be
someone I trust and love.

28:48.018 --> 28:50.521
Oh, I can help.

28:50.521 --> 28:52.356
- I'll be right back.
- Okay.

28:52.356 --> 28:54.108
[grunts]

28:54.108 --> 28:55.985
I love being dead!

28:55.985 --> 29:02.992
♪ ♪

29:15.463 --> 29:17.756
[June] Bananas!

29:17.756 --> 29:20.259
What?

29:20.259 --> 29:21.802
Bananas.

29:26.140 --> 29:28.309
Bananas are
the ideal beach food.

29:28.309 --> 29:32.062
They're handheld,
sweet but not bad for you,

29:32.062 --> 29:34.190
filling but not heavy,

29:34.190 --> 29:36.192
and the best part is,

29:36.192 --> 29:39.612
they come in their own wrapper
that protects them from sand.

29:43.449 --> 29:46.410
Which is biodegradable, so you
can throw it away anywhere.

29:46.410 --> 29:47.745
Exactly.

29:47.745 --> 29:49.997
Mm-hmm, bananas.

29:49.997 --> 29:52.041
That's the winner.

29:53.501 --> 29:56.045
I love you.

29:56.045 --> 29:58.047
I love you too.

29:58.047 --> 30:00.591
- I never should have left you.
- It's okay.

30:00.591 --> 30:02.676
You're here now.
That's all that matters.

30:07.932 --> 30:09.934
[exhales]

30:11.560 --> 30:13.354
So what do we do now?

30:14.813 --> 30:16.815
Should we go back
to Oceanside?

30:16.815 --> 30:19.985
No, I don't want
to go back to Oceanside.

30:22.446 --> 30:24.198
Maybe we should try
for Riverside again?

30:24.198 --> 30:25.658
There's got to be a way.

30:25.658 --> 30:28.244
No, we shouldn't
go backwards.

30:28.244 --> 30:29.286
Right.

30:29.286 --> 30:31.789
Let's find another way.

30:31.789 --> 30:33.123
We do have a boat.

30:34.792 --> 30:37.044
[Oscar grunts angrily]
[June] Oh, no!

30:37.044 --> 30:38.754
[Oscar] God damn it.

30:40.464 --> 30:42.550
No.

30:42.550 --> 30:45.469
- I worked really hard on this.
- It's okay.

30:45.469 --> 30:47.680
She was really impressive,
at least.

30:47.680 --> 30:49.807
Thanks.

30:49.807 --> 30:51.475
[exhales]

30:51.475 --> 30:53.227
Well, what now?

30:56.146 --> 30:58.440
I have an idea.

30:58.440 --> 31:00.943
Do you trust me?

31:00.943 --> 31:02.570
Of course.

31:06.865 --> 31:09.868
[soft music]

31:09.868 --> 31:16.875
♪ ♪

31:39.064 --> 31:46.071
♪ ♪

32:26.320 --> 32:33.327
♪ ♪

32:57.559 --> 33:01.271
[water lapping softly]

33:01.271 --> 33:04.274
[seagulls cawing]

33:10.781 --> 33:17.788
♪ ♪

33:28.215 --> 33:31.218
[♪ Novi Singers: "Mazurka in
A minor, Opus 17, Number 4"]

33:31.218 --> 33:34.221
[people vocalizing]

